of their way while they do their technical stuff, but I should also check if there\'s been any official communication about this vulnerability. Maybe I should check my email first to see if IT has sent out any guidance about what employees should do right now.\\n  - [ACTION:CONSULT] [@2026-04-09T00:23:05.337722]: {\\\\\\"kind\\\\\\": \\\\\\"mail\\\\\\", \\\\\\"service\\\\\\": \\\\\\"svc-email\\\\\\"}\\n  - [ACTION:DONE] [@2026-04-09T00:23:05.337722]: Checking email for official IT/security communications about the vulnerability while security_analyst_0 handles the technical response.\\n  - [STIMULUS:CONVERSATION] from security_analyst_0 [@2026-04-09T00:23:05.337722]: You\'re absolutely right to be concerned - any system handling candidate PII needs immediate attention. I\'m actively assessing the attack surface right now, but it\'s too early to confirm specific system compromise without thorough validation. I\'m starting with our SIEM to check for any exploitation attempts against recruiting platforms. I\'ll prioritize the candidate database and ATS systems in my triage, and will have concrete details on potential exposure within 30 minutes. Can you capture any suspicious emails or unusual access attempts to recruiting tools before we meet to update this at 2 PM?\\n"'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '"You can now produce your next sequence of actions for this turn, in order, and finish with DONE."'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '{"stimuli": [{"type": "CONVERSATION", "content": "You\'re absolutely right to be concerned - any system handling candidate PII needs immediate attention. I\'m actively assessing the attack surface right now, but it\'s too early to confirm specific system compromise without thorough validation. I\'m starting with our SIEM to check for any exploitation attempts against recruiting platforms. I\'ll prioritize the candidate database and ATS systems in my triage, and will have concrete details on potential exposure within 30 minutes. Can you capture any suspicious emails or unusual access attempts to recruiting tools before we meet to update this at 2 PM?", "source": "security_analyst_0"}]}'}]
